    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "ucf_threshold_probe",
    "description": "2-scenario bracketing probe to narrow the user_custody_fraction (ucf) reversal threshold identified in user_weight_mini_test.\nKNOWN BOUNDS (from mini_test): - ucf=0.01, split=0.50 \u2192 v27 wins  (sweep_0000) - ucf=0.65, split=0.50 \u2192 v26 wins  (sweep_0002, reversal via econ dilution)\nThreshold is somewhere in [0.01, 0.65]. This probe places two points from the user_weight_threshold.yaml full grid to pre-compute the most informative bracket: - ucf=0.20 (lower quarter \u2014 does dilution kick in this early?) - ucf=0.35 (near midpoint \u2014 near the Foundry flip-point, most contested region)\nDECISION TABLE:\n  ucf=0.20   ucf=0.35   \u2192 interpretation\n  v27 wins   v27 wins   \u2192 threshold > 0.35, narrows to [0.35, 0.65]\n  v27 wins   v26 wins   \u2192 threshold between 0.20\u20130.35 (tight bracket)\n  v26 wins   v26 wins   \u2192 threshold < 0.20 (surprisingly low, strong user effect)\n\nuser_split fixed at 0.50 (neutral) \u2014 the adversarial dilution case that produced the reversal. This is the minimum-influence scenario, giving the strongest possible null bound.\nRUNTIME: 1 namespace, ~7.2 hours sequential (2 \u00d7 3.6 hrs). NOTE: Both scenarios are grid members of user_weight_threshold.yaml (ucf \u2208 {0.20, 0.35}, split=0.50), so these results feed directly into tomorrow's full 30-scenario run.\n",
